body:
One indication of proper curing in epoxies is the glass transition temperature. For these samples, there was no change in the glass transition temperature for 5, 10, 15phr and even for 20phr NT-Al2O3 nanocomposites, which indicates that the crosslink density of the epoxy resin did not change significantly upon nanoparticle addition ([tbl1]
                        ). For the APTES–Al2O3 nanocomposites, the glass transition temperatures decreased slightly at low filler concentration, which might be due to the soft silane layers formed on the surface of Al2O3 nanoparticles. An 11°C drop was observed for 20phr APTES–Al2O3/epoxy nanocomposite. However, DSC tests of the curing reaction showed complete cure of the nanocomposites. At this time, the decrease in <i>T</i>
                        g is not well understood.
